SIMPLE: pestilential
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pestilential
<hw>Pes`ti*len"tial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pestilentiel</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the nature or
qualities of a pestilence.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Sends the
<xex>pestilential</xex> vapors.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Longfellow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence: Mischievous; noxious; pernicious; morally
destructive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So <qex>pestilential</qex>, so infectious a thing is sin.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pestilentially</ent>⟦br⟧
